// @run
// @log 12
// @log 12
// @log 7
// Trailing comma in a call argument list (`f(a, b,)`). VL formerly rejected this
// — the trailing `,` is now allowed and ignored, so a multi-line call list can
// carry one for cleaner diffs. The result is identical to the comma-free form.
function add(a: i32, b: i32) a + b
print(add(5, 7))
print(add(5, 7,))
print(
  add(
    3,
    4,
  ),
)
